General Motors hope sell 7,000 8,000 North American-made vehicle Europe year , five-fold rise year , James Fry , vice- president GM Overseas Distribution Corporation said .
`` The low dollar make price attractive , '' told news briefing opening Geneva Motor Show .
`` We would like sell 7,000 8,000 unit Europe year August 1987 , '' told Reuters later .
Officials said GM sold 1,500 North American-made vehicle 1986 model year .
